    //String concatenation in Java
    //There are 2 types of concatenation strings in Java
    //Type 1: By + (string concatenation) operator
    //Type 2: by Concat() method
    /*let's look at the  first type by + (String concatenation) operator
    Java String concatenation operator (+) is used to add strings. 
    Example:*/
    /*class Main {
      public static void main(String args[]){
        String s = "Brirth"+"day";
        System.out.println(s);
        //A piece of java compiler transform the above to this;
        String s = (new StringBuilder()).append("Birh").append("day").toString();
      }
    }*/
        //String concatenation by using concat() method
        // The string concat () method concatenates the specified string to the end of current string. Here is syntax:
        //public String concat(String another);

        //now let's see an Example
        class Main { 
          public static void main (String[]){
            String s1 = "Birth";
            String s2 = "day";
            String s3 = s1 concat (s2);
            System.out.println(s3);
          }
        }
